{
  "texts": [
    "When this dampening hyperparameter is set too small, s test estimation can diverge (Yeh et al., 2018; Hara et al., 2019; Hammoudeh & Lowd, 2022).",
    "More generally, Basu et al. (2021) show that training hyperparameters also significantly affect influence functions' performance.",
    "Specifically, Basu et al. (2021) empirically demonstrate that model initialization, model width, model depth, weight-decay strength, and even the test instance being analyzed (z te) all can negatively affect influence functions' LOO estimation accuracy.",
    "Their finding is supported by the analysis of Zhang & Zhang (2022) who show that HVP estimation's accuracy depends heavily on the model's training regularizer with HVP accuracy \"pretty low under weak regularization.\"",
    "Bae et al. (2022) also empirically analyze the potential sources of influence functions' fragility on deep models."
  ]
}